        </div>
      </form>
      <br/>


      <p>
        <b>Summary.</b> The bigger the force that is acting on an object in the direction of its motion, the more the
        object will speed up in the direction of the force <i>while that force is acting on the object</i>. As the hill
        gets steeper, the part of the force of gravity that acts down the hill increases. So, the object's speed
        increases more quickly (or the acceleration increases) as the hill gets steeper.
      </p>
